title: Manned mini-sub vanishes near Titanic wreck, search efforts underway
description: A submersible used to take tourists to the wreck of the Titanic has vanished in the Atlantic Ocean.

title: Navalny’s new trial on ‘extremism’ is held in secret, in a prison
description: Russia's leading opposition figure, already imprisoned on charges viewed as political retribution, is now being accused of running an extremist group: his foundation that long fought public corruption.

title: On Boris Johnson’s birthday, Parliament set to deal him humiliating blow
description: Parliament will debate the scathing Partygate report and is expected to endorse its findings and withdraw Johnson's parliamentary pass.

title: A week after reviving at her wake, woman is now dead, doctors say
description: Bella Montoya, an Ecuadoran woman who was declared dead but later heard knocking on her coffin, has been declared dead again after a week in intensive care.

title: Ukraine live briefing: Zelensky praises troops for limited gains in counteroffensive battles
description: The United Nations called out Moscow for blocking humanitarian aid shipments to Russian-controlled areas of Ukraine affected by the Kakhovka dam collapse.

title: Facebook helped bring free speech to Vietnam. Now it’s helping stifle it.
description: Meta, which owns Facebook, has been censoring dissent and allowing those seen as threats by the regime in Vietnam to be forced off the platform, former employees and others say

title: Blinken may meet China’s Xi Jinping in effort to soothe tensions
description: If confirmed, the talks will cap two days of meetings aimed at lowering tensions between the two superpowers, although the most bitterly contested issues remain unresolved.

title: Ukraine clamps down on corruption as Western supporters cast watchful eye
description: In Kyiv, Ukrainian officials are working to root out graft, reassure financial backers and secure the country’s path to membership in the European Union.
